data.title: Watchpoint Game Night Part 1
data.description: In our first edition of Watchpoint Game night, some of the league’s best players square off versus on-air talent in some of your favorite living room games.

data.title: Reigning Over ATL
data.description: Back in Blizzard Arena for the first time since the Atlanta Homestand, the Atlanta Reign’s Dogman and Babybay recount what it was like playing for the home crowd and how they were given a proper “Down South” welcome.

data.title: 1v1 with EQO and Sinatraa
data.description: With damage dealers popping off in Stage 4, we brought in two of the best damage players, EQO and Sinatraa, to sit down and talk about what they’re excited about and who they have their eyes on as they move towards playoffs.

data.title: The 2019 Overwatch League MVP Candidates
data.description: The time has come to immortalize another player in the halls of esports legends. Who will you choose to be the 2019 Overwatch League MVP presented by T-Mobile? Vote on Twitter using #OWLMVP and the players battle tag or directly on Twitch. Now is your chance to be a part of history: vote for the 2019 Overwatch League MVP presented by T-Mobile. Learn more: overwatchleague.com/mvp

data.title: Tactics: Seoul Dynasty Clutches a 3v6 with less than 10 Seconds Left
data.description: No matter how one-sided an Overwatch teamfight is looking, it's truly never over until it's actually over. In this episode of Tactics, we review an Overtime teamfight that the Seoul Dynasty miraculously clutched vs. the Chengdu Hunters when they were at a massive numbers disadvantage with only seconds left in their time bank. It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: Introducing League Picks
data.description: Make correct predictions for Overwatch League matches, complete challenges, and earn League Tokens.

data.title: LA Gladiators Hydration and BigGoose Paint: Access Granted
data.description: Get your shields up as Chris Puckett picks up Hydration and BigGoose of the LA Gladiators and head off to paint some pottery. Hear about their fine dining tastes and finally learn the lyrics to the Gladiator's hype song in this episode of Access Granted presented by Toyota.

data.title: Hangzhou Spark’s guxue and Krystal: Access Granted
data.description: Overwatch League insider Emily Tang picks up guxue and Krystal of the Hangzhou Spark to go check out a cat cafe. Hear all about the music that get these pros in the zone before taking the stage, as well as what players they admire in the league. This is Access Granted presented by Toyota.

data.title: Meta Report: Stage 3
data.description: Hear from Overwatch League's own Mr. X, MonteCristo, Sideshow, and Wolf as they break down the changes we've seen in the Stage 3 meta and which teams have improved the most. It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: Pressure Rising: Fighting for Playoffs
data.description: As the books begin to close on Stage 4 and the 2019 Overwatch League season, the last remaining eligible teams sound off on their scramble to the playoffs.

data.title: Did You Catch That? Shax’s 6K ALMOST Interrupted!
data.description: In this first episode of "Did You Catch That?", we slow the action down on LA Valiant Shax's 6-man Reaper Death Blossom to highlight just how close he was to being shut down by the Seoul Dynasty! "Did You Catch That?" is an educational series that highlights exceptional moments in the Overwatch League that might have happened too quickly to catch! It’s all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: Overwatch League MVP Pro-File: guxue
data.description: In this Overwatch League MVP Pro-File we go bananas for the best Winston in the League, guxue. Representing the Chinese scene, guxue made a name for himself at the Overwatch World Cup. Since joining the Overwatch League with the Hangzhou Spark, guxue has overcome the language barriers to establish his team as one of the best in the league. Cast your vote now for this year’s MVP on twitter using #OWLMVP plus your favorite player’s BattleTag. Now is your chance to be a part of history: vote for the Overwatch League MVP presented by T-Mobile.

data.title: Overwatch League MVP Pro-Files: sinatraa
data.description: In this Overwatch League MVP Pro-File we're talking all about sinatraa. Signed to the San Francisco Shock before he was old enough to play, sinatraa was originally known for his Tracer. As the meta shifted, sinatraa proved he was the real deal by easily transitioning to playing Zarya, quickly becoming one of the best in the League.
